<node id="8">
  <data key="d0">The search results provide conflicting information about the honor for which the Leipzig 1877 tournament was organized. One source (Wikipedia on Adolf Anderssen) states that the tournament was organized in honor of Adolf Anderssen, named the "Anderssen-Feier" (Anderssen Celebration). Another source from Oxen.ai mentions it was organized in honor of Wilhelm Steinitz becoming the first official World Chess Champion. Additional sources mention honoring Anderssen's 50th anniversary of learning chess. To resolve this conflict and provide a definitive answer, I should look for more authoritative sources or historical records specifically about the Leipzig 1877 tournament and its dedication.</data>
  <data key="d1">The search results provide conflicting information about the honor for which the Leipzig 1877 tourna...</data>
